[{"id":"VR024045","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two sets of metal spheres on insulating stands. Each set has three spheres labeled A through C from left to right. In the first set of spheres, which is on the left, spheres A and B are a short distance apart, and spheres B and C are touching. In the second set of spheres, which is on the right, spheres A and B are a short distance apart, and spheres B and C are a longer distance apart than spheres A and B.\" height=\"68\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR024045.g01.png\" width=\"300\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figures above represent three metal spheres on insulating stands. Initially sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and spheres <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are uncharged. Spheres <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are in contact when sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is brought near sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> but does not touch it, as shown on the left. Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is then separated from sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, as shown on the right. Which of the following best describes the final charges on spheres <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR024045_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"></p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup cols:2\"><colgroup><col class=\"colspec align:center\"><col class=\"colspec align:center\"></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\">Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> </th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> </th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">Positive </td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Uncharged </td></tr></tbody></table></div>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"></p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup cols:2\"><colgroup><col class=\"colspec align:center\"><col class=\"colspec align:center\"></colgroup><t